<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <meta name="description" content="DNS Pilot privacy policy for the Store-safe macOS app.">
  <link rel="canonical" href="{{SITE_URL}}/privacy.html">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <title>DNS Pilot Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">DNS Pilot</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Current Store-safe macOS build.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Collection and Tracking</h2>
      <p>DNS Pilot does not collect personal data, track users across apps or websites, include analytics, use advertising SDKs, or include third-party tracking SDKs.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Data</h2>
      <p>DNS Pilot stores custom DNS profiles, custom domain test suites, benchmark history, app language, and guided-apply state locally on the Mac. This data is used only to provide app features on that device.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Network Activity</h2>
      <p>When the user runs a benchmark, DNS Pilot sends user-initiated DNS, TCP, and optional connection-path probes to selected DNS resolvers and target domains. These requests are required for the benchmark feature.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>System DNS Changes</h2>
      <p>The Store-safe macOS build does not silently change system DNS. Guided Apply copies DNS servers and opens macOS Network Settings for the user to make the OS-level change.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p><a href="mailto:{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}">{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer><a href="index.html">Support</a></footer>
</body>
</html>
